The previous add command stores a qeustion instance which is also stored in the main bank. When edit command is executed, this question is modified and when the edit is undone, the question bank replace that question with a new instance of question that has its original state. Then undo the AddCommand will cause error because the the restored question does not match the question stored in AddCommand class. This issue is now fixed with adding a new attribute to the AddCommand class that stores the original state of the question it added.

commitResults.messageBody:
Adds True False question type

Updates the rated documentation for it and related features.

Improve the overall quality of code primarily on AddCommand class and EditCommand class, together with minor changes on some data classes.
Now edit and add properly detect duplication of questions based on question content only, i.e. two questions cannot have the same question content even if they are of different class type.
A duplicate in question will result in termination of add/edit command, because it is very unlikely a user will try to log 2 identical questions, and if they do, there is no point to proceed and force them to add a redundant question to complete the command process.
MCQ now properly detect duplication in options during add and edit process. A duplicate in options will not result in termination of the current process but the user will be prompted to enter a valid option.
Updated project documentation on relavant parts.
Removed manageMultistepCommand() method from parser class because it is redundant. The logic is already been handled in the main class. The parser class should only parse the user input, and therefore handling multistep logic is irrelevant to parsing.

Edit is now properly traced.
Update relevant DG/UG.

Important
-a high severity bug is found and reported as issue.
-now Question class have overriding equals() method that compare two questions only based on their question content.
The rationale is that this helps the storage of state of questions. We can also justify in UG/DG that we do not allow duplicate in questions based on question content because it is not really helpful to have
FITB: Which continent is France located?
and
MCQ: Which continent is France located?
A. Europe
B. Asia
C. North America
D. Africa
at the same time.
Clarify the handling of inputting random strings for MCQ or TF
